{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"A talk about surgical robots"},{"time":3000,"text":"is also a talk about surgery."},{"time":6000,"text":"And while I've tried to make my images not too graphic,"},{"time":10000,"text":"keep in mind that surgeons have a different relationship with blood"},{"time":13000,"text":"than normal people do,"},{"time":15000,"text":"because, after all, what a surgeon does to a patient,"},{"time":19000,"text":"if it were done without consent,"},{"time":21000,"text":"would be a felony."},{"time":24000,"text":"Surgeons are the tailors, the plumbers,"},{"time":28000,"text":"the carpenters -- some would say the butchers --"},{"time":30000,"text":"of the medical world:"},{"time":32000,"text":"cutting, reshaping, reforming,"},{"time":35000,"text":"bypassing, fixing."},{"time":38000,"text":"But you need to talk about surgical instruments"},{"time":42000,"text":"and the evolution of surgical technology together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"So in order to give you some kind of a perspective"},{"time":49000,"text":"of where we are right now"},{"time":51000,"text":"with surgical robots,"},{"time":53000,"text":"and where we're going to be going in the future,"},{"time":55000,"text":"I want to give you a little bit of perspective"},{"time":57000,"text":"of how we got to this point,"},{"time":59000,"text":"how we even came to believe"},{"time":62000,"text":"that surgery was OK,"},{"time":64000,"text":"that this was something that was possible to do,"},{"time":66000,"text":"that this kind of cutting and reforming was OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"So, a little bit of perspective --"},{"time":73000,"text":"about 10,000 years of perspective."},{"time":76000,"text":"This is a trephinated skull."},{"time":79000,"text":"And trephination is simply just cutting a hole in the skull."},{"time":83000,"text":"And many, many hundreds of skulls like this"},{"time":85000,"text":"have been found in archaeological sites"},{"time":88000,"text":"all over the world,"},{"time":90000,"text":"dating back five to 10 thousand years."},{"time":94000,"text":"Five to 10 thousand years! Now imagine this."},{"time":98000,"text":"You are a healer in a Stone Age village."},{"time":101000,"text":"And you have some guy that you're not quite sure what's wrong with him --"},{"time":104000,"text":"Oliver Sacks is going to be born way in the future."},{"time":107000,"text":"He's got some seizure disorder. And you don't understand this."},{"time":110000,"text":"But you think to yourself,"},{"time":112000,"text":"\"I'm not quite sure what's wrong with this guy."},{"time":114000,"text":"But maybe if I cut a hole in his head I can fix it.\""},{"time":117000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":118000,"text":"Now that is surgical thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"Now we've got the dawn of interventional surgery here."},{"time":124000,"text":"What is astonishing about this is,"},{"time":126000,"text":"even though we don't know really how much of this"},{"time":130000,"text":"was intended to be religious,"},{"time":133000,"text":"or how much of it was intended to be therapeutic,"},{"time":136000,"text":"what we can tell is that these patients lived!"},{"time":139000,"text":"Judging by the healing on the borders of these holes,"},{"time":141000,"text":"they lived days, months, years following trephination."},{"time":146000,"text":"And so what we are seeing is evidence"},{"time":149000,"text":"of a refined technique"},{"time":151000,"text":"that was being handed down over thousands and thousands of years,"},{"time":154000,"text":"all over the world."},{"time":156000,"text":"This arose independently at sites everywhere"},{"time":158000,"text":"that had no communication to one another."},{"time":161000,"text":"We really are seeing the dawn of interventional surgery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"Now we can fast forward many thousands of years"},{"time":168000,"text":"into the Bronze Age and beyond."},{"time":170000,"text":"And we see new refined tools coming out."},{"time":173000,"text":"But surgeons in these eras are a little bit more conservative"},{"time":176000,"text":"than their bold, trephinating ancestors."},{"time":179000,"text":"These guys confined their surgery"},{"time":181000,"text":"to fairly superficial injuries."},{"time":183000,"text":"And surgeons were tradesmen,"},{"time":185000,"text":"rather than physicians."},{"time":188000,"text":"This persisted all the way into and through the Renaissance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"That may have saved the writers,"},{"time":194000,"text":"but it didn't really save the surgeons terribly much."},{"time":197000,"text":"They were still a mistrusted lot."},{"time":200000,"text":"Surgeons still had a bit of a PR problem,"},{"time":203000,"text":"because the landscape was dominated"},{"time":205000,"text":"by the itinerant barber surgeon."},{"time":207000,"text":"These were folks that traveled from village to village, town to town,"},{"time":211000,"text":"doing surgery sort of as a form of performance art."},{"time":215000,"text":"Because we were in the age before anesthesia,"},{"time":217000,"text":"the agony of the patient"},{"time":219000,"text":"is really as much of the public spectacle"},{"time":221000,"text":"as the surgery itself."},{"time":224000,"text":"One of the most famous of these guys, Frere Jacques,"},{"time":227000,"text":"shown here doing a lithotomy --"},{"time":230000,"text":"which is the removal of the bladder stone,"},{"time":232000,"text":"one of the most invasive surgeries they did at the time --"},{"time":234000,"text":"had to take less than two minutes."},{"time":237000,"text":"You had to have quite a flair for the dramatic,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and be really, really quick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"And so here you see him doing a lithotomy."},{"time":244000,"text":"And he is credited with doing over 4,000 of these public surgeries,"},{"time":248000,"text":"wandering around in Europe,"},{"time":250000,"text":"which is an astonishing number,"},{"time":252000,"text":"when you think that surgery must have been a last resort."},{"time":256000,"text":"I mean who would put themselves through that?"},{"time":259000,"text":"Until anesthesia, the absence of sensation."},{"time":265000,"text":"With the demonstration of the Morton Ether Inhaler"},{"time":268000,"text":"at the Mass. General in 1847,"},{"time":271000,"text":"a whole new era of surgery was ushered in."},{"time":274000,"text":"Anesthesia gave surgeons the freedom to operate."},{"time":278000,"text":"Anesthesia gave them the freedom to experiment,"},{"time":280000,"text":"to start to delve deeper into the body."},{"time":284000,"text":"This was truly a revolution in surgery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"But there was a pretty big problem with this."},{"time":290000,"text":"After these very long, painstaking operations,"},{"time":293000,"text":"attempting to cure things they'd never been able to touch before,"},{"time":297000,"text":"the patients died."},{"time":301000,"text":"They died of massive infection."},{"time":305000,"text":"Surgery didn't hurt anymore,"},{"time":307000,"text":"but it killed you pretty quickly."},{"time":309000,"text":"And infection would continue to claim a majority of surgical patients"},{"time":314000,"text":"until the next big revolution in surgery,"},{"time":317000,"text":"which was aseptic technique."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"Joseph Lister was aepsis's,"},{"time":323000,"text":"or sterility's, biggest advocate,"},{"time":326000,"text":"to a very very skeptical bunch of surgeons."},{"time":329000,"text":"But eventually they did come around."},{"time":331000,"text":"The Mayo brothers came out to visit Lister in Europe."},{"time":335000,"text":"And they came back to their American clinic and they said"},{"time":337000,"text":"they had learned it was as important to wash your hands"},{"time":340000,"text":"before doing surgery"},{"time":342000,"text":"as it was to wash up afterwards. (Laughter)"},{"time":345000,"text":"Something so simple."},{"time":347000,"text":"And yet, operative mortality dropped profoundly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"These surgeries were actually now being effective."},{"time":354000,"text":"With the patient insensitive to pain,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and a sterile operating field"},{"time":361000,"text":"all bets were off, the sky was the limit."},{"time":365000,"text":"You could now start doing surgery everywhere,"},{"time":370000,"text":"on the gut, on the liver,"},{"time":373000,"text":"on the heart, on the brain."},{"time":375000,"text":"Transplantation: you could take an organ out of one person,"},{"time":377000,"text":"you could put it in another person, and it would work."},{"time":380000,"text":"Surgeons didn't have a problem with respectability anymore;"},{"time":383000,"text":"they had become gods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"The era of the \"big surgeon, big incision\" had arrived,"},{"time":391000,"text":"but at quite a cost,"},{"time":394000,"text":"because they are saving lives,"},{"time":396000,"text":"but not necessarily quality of life,"},{"time":400000,"text":"because healthy people don't usually need surgery,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and unhealthy people have a very hard time recovering from a cut like that."},{"time":408000,"text":"The question had to be asked,"},{"time":410000,"text":"\"Well, can we do these same surgeries"},{"time":413000,"text":"but through little incisions?\""},{"time":417000,"text":"Laparoscopy is doing this kind of surgery:"},{"time":420000,"text":"surgery with long instruments through small incisions."},{"time":423000,"text":"And it really changed the landscape of surgery."},{"time":427000,"text":"Some of the tools for this had been around for a hundred years,"},{"time":431000,"text":"but it had only been used as a diagnostic technique"},{"time":433000,"text":"until the 1980s,"},{"time":435000,"text":"when there was changes in camera technologies and things like that,"},{"time":438000,"text":"that allowed this to be done for real operations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"So what you see -- this is now the first surgical image --"},{"time":445000,"text":"as we're coming down the tube, this is a new entry into the body."},{"time":449000,"text":"It looks very different from what you're expecting surgery to look like."},{"time":452000,"text":"We bring instruments in,"},{"time":454000,"text":"from two separate cuts in the side,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and then you can start manipulating tissue."},{"time":460000,"text":"Within 10 years of the first gallbladder surgeries"},{"time":463000,"text":"being done laparoscopically,"},{"time":466000,"text":"a majority of gallbladder surgeries"},{"time":468000,"text":"were being done laparoscopically --"},{"time":471000,"text":"truly a pretty big revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"But there were casualties of this revolution."},{"time":480000,"text":"These techniques were a lot harder to learn"},{"time":482000,"text":"than people had anticipated."},{"time":484000,"text":"The learning curve was very long."},{"time":486000,"text":"And during that learning curve the complications went quite a bit higher."},{"time":490000,"text":"Surgeons had to give up their 3D vision."},{"time":492000,"text":"They had to give up their wrists."},{"time":494000,"text":"They had to give up intuitive motion in the instruments."},{"time":499000,"text":"This surgeon has over 3,000 hours of laparoscopic experience."},{"time":505000,"text":"Now this is a particularly frustrating placement of the needle."},{"time":510000,"text":"But this is hard."},{"time":512000,"text":"And one of the reasons why it is so hard"},{"time":515000,"text":"is because the external ergonomics are terrible."},{"time":519000,"text":"You've got these long instruments, and you're working off your centerline."},{"time":523000,"text":"And the instruments are essentially working backwards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"So what you need to do, to take the capability of your hand,"},{"time":531000,"text":"and put it on the other side of that small incision,"},{"time":534000,"text":"is you need to put a wrist on that instrument."},{"time":539000,"text":"And so -- I get to talk about robots --"},{"time":541000,"text":"the da Vinci robot"},{"time":543000,"text":"put just that wrist on the other side of that incision."},{"time":547000,"text":"And so here you're seeing the operation of this wrist."},{"time":550000,"text":"And now, in contrast to the laparoscopy,"},{"time":553000,"text":"you can precisely place the needle in your instruments,"},{"time":556000,"text":"and you can pass it all the way through"},{"time":559000,"text":"and follow it in a trajectory."},{"time":561000,"text":"And the reason why this becomes so much easier"},{"time":563000,"text":"is -- you can see on the bottom --"},{"time":566000,"text":"the hands are making the motions,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and the instruments are following those motions exactly."},{"time":573000,"text":"Now, what you put between those instruments and those hands,"},{"time":577000,"text":"is a large, fairly complicated robot."},{"time":579000,"text":"The surgeon is sitting at a console,"},{"time":581000,"text":"and controlling the robot with these controllers."},{"time":585000,"text":"And the robot is moving these instruments around,"},{"time":588000,"text":"and powering them, down inside the body."},{"time":591000,"text":"You have a 3D camera, so you get a 3D view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594000,"text":"And since this was introduced in 1999,"},{"time":598000,"text":"a lot of these robots have been out"},{"time":600000,"text":"and being used for surgical procedures like a prostatectomy,"},{"time":604000,"text":"which is a prostate deep in the pelvis,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and it requires fine dissection"},{"time":609000,"text":"and delicate manipulation"},{"time":611000,"text":"to be able to get a good surgical outcome."},{"time":614000,"text":"You can also sew bypass vessels directly onto a beating heart"},{"time":619000,"text":"without cracking the chest."},{"time":622000,"text":"This is all done in between the ribs."},{"time":624000,"text":"And you can go inside the heart itself"},{"time":627000,"text":"and repair the valves from the inside."},{"time":631000,"text":"You've got these technologies -- thank you --"},{"time":634000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":637000,"text":"And so you might say, \"Wow this is really cool!"},{"time":639000,"text":"So, smartypants, why isn't all surgery being done this way?\""},{"time":642000,"text":"And there are some reasons, some good reasons."},{"time":645000,"text":"And cost is one of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"I talked about the large, complicated robot."},{"time":649000,"text":"With all its bells and whistles, one of those robots"},{"time":652000,"text":"will cost you about as much as a solid gold surgeon."},{"time":655000,"text":"More useful than a solid gold surgeon,"},{"time":657000,"text":"but, still, it's a fairly big capital investment."},{"time":661000,"text":"But once you've got it, your procedure costs do come down."},{"time":667000,"text":"But there are other barriers."},{"time":669000,"text":"So something like a prostatectomy --"},{"time":672000,"text":"the prostate is small, and it's in one spot,"},{"time":674000,"text":"and you can set your robot up very precisely"},{"time":677000,"text":"to work in that one spot."},{"time":679000,"text":"And so it's perfect for something like that."},{"time":681000,"text":"And in fact if you, or anyone you know,"},{"time":683000,"text":"had their prostate taken out in the last couple of years,"},{"time":685000,"text":"chances are it was done with one of these systems."},{"time":689000,"text":"But if you need to reach more places than just one,"},{"time":693000,"text":"you need to move the robot."},{"time":695000,"text":"And you need to put some new incisions in there."},{"time":697000,"text":"And you need to re-set it up."},{"time":700000,"text":"And then you need to add some more ports, and more."},{"time":704000,"text":"And the problem is it gets time-consuming, and cumbersome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"And for that reason there are many surgeries"},{"time":709000,"text":"that just aren't being done with the da Vinci."},{"time":713000,"text":"So we had to ask the question, \"Well how do we fix that?\""},{"time":718000,"text":"What if we could change it so that we didn't have to re-set up"},{"time":722000,"text":"each time we wanted to move somewhere different?"},{"time":724000,"text":"What if we could bring all the instruments"},{"time":726000,"text":"in together in one place?"},{"time":728000,"text":"How would that change the capabilities of the surgeon?"},{"time":732000,"text":"And how would that change the experience for the patient?"},{"time":736000,"text":"Now, to do that,"},{"time":738000,"text":"we need to be able to bring a camera"},{"time":741000,"text":"and instruments in together through one small tube,"},{"time":745000,"text":"like that tube you saw in the laparoscopy video."},{"time":748000,"text":"Or, not so coincidentally, like a tube like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"So what's going to come out of that tube"},{"time":756000,"text":"is the debut of this new technology,"},{"time":759000,"text":"this new robot that is going to be able to reach anywhere."},{"time":764000,"text":"Ready? So here it comes."},{"time":768000,"text":"This is the camera, and three instruments."},{"time":771000,"text":"And as you see it come out,"},{"time":773000,"text":"in order to actually be able to do anything useful,"},{"time":775000,"text":"it can't all stay clustered up like this."},{"time":778000,"text":"It has to be able to come off of the centerline"},{"time":781000,"text":"and then be able to work back toward that centerline."},{"time":785000,"text":"He's a cheeky little devil."},{"time":788000,"text":"But what this lets you do"},{"time":790000,"text":"is gives you that all-important traction,"},{"time":792000,"text":"and counter-traction,"},{"time":794000,"text":"so that you can dissect, so that you can sew,"},{"time":796000,"text":"so that you can do all the things that you need to do,"},{"time":798000,"text":"all the surgical tasks."},{"time":800000,"text":"But it's all coming in through one incision."},{"time":804000,"text":"It's not so simple."},{"time":807000,"text":"But it's worth it for the freedom that this gives us"},{"time":810000,"text":"as we're going around."},{"time":812000,"text":"For the patient, however,"},{"time":816000,"text":"it's transparent. This is all they're going to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"It's very exciting to think where we get to go with this."},{"time":826000,"text":"We get to write the script of the next revolution in surgery."},{"time":831000,"text":"As we take these capabilities, and we get to go to the next places,"},{"time":835000,"text":"we get to decide what our new surgeries are going to be."},{"time":839000,"text":"And I think to really get the rest of the way"},{"time":841000,"text":"in that revolution,"},{"time":843000,"text":"we need to not just take our hands in in new ways,"},{"time":846000,"text":"we also need to take our eyes in in new ways."},{"time":850000,"text":"We need to see beyond the surface."},{"time":852000,"text":"We need to be able to guide what we're cutting"},{"time":855000,"text":"in a much better way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860000,"text":"This is a cancer surgery."},{"time":862000,"text":"One of the problems with this,"},{"time":864000,"text":"even for surgeons who've been looking at this a lot,"},{"time":866000,"text":"is you can't see the cancer,"},{"time":869000,"text":"especially when it's hidden below the surface."},{"time":872000,"text":"And so what we're starting to do"},{"time":874000,"text":"is we're starting to inject specially designed markers"},{"time":878000,"text":"into the bloodstream that will target the cancer."},{"time":881000,"text":"It will go, bind to the cancer."},{"time":884000,"text":"And we can make those markers glow."},{"time":887000,"text":"And we can take special cameras,"},{"time":889000,"text":"and we can look at it."},{"time":892000,"text":"Now we know where we need to cut,"},{"time":894000,"text":"even when it's below the surface."},{"time":897000,"text":"We can take these markers and we can inject them in a tumor site."},{"time":901000,"text":"And we can follow where they flow out from that tumor site,"},{"time":905000,"text":"so we can see the first places where that cancer might travel."},{"time":911000,"text":"We can inject these dyes into the bloodstream,"},{"time":914000,"text":"so that when we do a new vessel"},{"time":917000,"text":"and we bypass a blockage on the heart,"},{"time":919000,"text":"we can see if we actually made the connection,"},{"time":922000,"text":"before we close that patient back up again --"},{"time":925000,"text":"something that we haven't been able to do"},{"time":927000,"text":"without radiation before."},{"time":930000,"text":"We can light up tumors"},{"time":933000,"text":"like this kidney tumor,"},{"time":935000,"text":"so that you can exactly see where the boundary is"},{"time":938000,"text":"between the kidney tumor and the kidney you want to leave behind,"},{"time":942000,"text":"or the liver tumor and the liver you want to leave behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946000,"text":"And we don't even need to confine ourselves"},{"time":949000,"text":"to this macro vision."},{"time":952000,"text":"We have flexible microscopic probes"},{"time":954000,"text":"that we can bring down into the body."},{"time":957000,"text":"And we can look at cells directly."},{"time":960000,"text":"I'm looking at nerves here. So these are nerves you see, down on the bottom,"},{"time":963000,"text":"and the microscope probe that's being held by the robotic hand, up at the top."},{"time":967000,"text":"So this is all very prototypey at this point."},{"time":970000,"text":"But you care about nerves, if you are a surgical patient."},{"time":973000,"text":"Because they let you keep continence,"},{"time":976000,"text":"bladder control, and sexual function after surgery,"},{"time":980000,"text":"all of which is generally fairly important to the patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"So, with the combination of these technologies"},{"time":990000,"text":"we can reach it all, and we can see it all."},{"time":994000,"text":"We can heal the disease."},{"time":997000,"text":"And we can leave the patient whole and intact"},{"time":1001000,"text":"and functional afterwards."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Now, I've talked about the patient"},{"time":1007000,"text":"as if the patient is, somehow, someone abstract"},{"time":1010000,"text":"outside this room."},{"time":1012000,"text":"And that is not the case."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Many of you, all of you maybe,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"will at some point, or have already, faced a diagnosis of cancer,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"or heart disease, or some organ dysfunction"},{"time":1024000,"text":"that's going to buy you a date with a surgeon."},{"time":1027000,"text":"And when you get to that point --"},{"time":1031000,"text":"I mean, these maladies don't care"},{"time":1034000,"text":"how many books you've written,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"how many companies you've started,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"that Nobel Prize you have yet to win,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"how much time you planned to spend with your children."},{"time":1045000,"text":"These maladies come for us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1048000,"text":"And the prospect I'm offering you, of an easier surgery ..."},{"time":1050000,"text":"is that going to make that diagnosis any less terrifying?"},{"time":1055000,"text":"I'm not sure I really even want it to."},{"time":1059000,"text":"Because facing your own mortality"},{"time":1062000,"text":"causes a re-evaluation of priorities,"},{"time":1065000,"text":"and a realignment of what your goals are in life, unlike anything else."},{"time":1070000,"text":"And I would never want to deprive you of that epiphany."},{"time":1075000,"text":"What I want instead,"},{"time":1078000,"text":"is for you to be whole, intact,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"and functional enough to go out and save the world,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"after you've decided you need to do it."},{"time":1091000,"text":"And that is my vision for your future."},{"time":1094000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1096000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}